    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, serverlist is a different thing in Vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nrxvt-unicode (urxvt) v9.30 - released: 2021-11-27\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-color\n\n### Installation\n\nArch linux community package\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nIn separate terminals:\r\n\r\nnvim --clean --listen /tmp/neovim\r\nnvim --clean --listen /tmp/neovim2\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect that `:echo serverlist()` in either of these nvim instances would print `['/tmp/neovim', 'tmp/neovim2']`\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nRunning `:echo serverlist()` in these two instances only returns their own server names -- `['/tmp/neovim']` and `['/tmp/neovim2']`. This also happens with TCP, e.g. `127.0.0.1:5001`.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "serverlist() returns all servers started by the current Nvim's `serverstart()`. This is a known issue.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/18993 was a step towards making non-TCP servers \"discoverable\" by iterating through the parent dir of `stdpath('run')`.",
