            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I just learned about --listen and tried to add neovim support to https://github.com/AndrewRadev/vimrunner\r\n\r\ncool! fwiw meanwhile, `:help serverstart()` documents this shell one-liner to list all (unix socket) servers:\r\n\r\n    ls ${XDG_RUNTIME_DIR:-${TMPDIR}nvim.${USER}}/*/nvim.*.0\r\n\r\nprobably better to use `find ... -type s`:\r\n\r\n    find ${XDG_RUNTIME_DIR:-${TMPDIR}nvim.${USER}}/ -type s\r\n\r\n> It would also be convenient to export it as `--serverlist`, similar to what Vim provides, though I can work around its lack.\r\n\r\nThis should be equivalent (planning to make a change so that `-V1` is less noisy):\r\n\r\n    nvim -es -V1 +\"echo join(serverlist(),'\\n')\"",
