            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "To fix this, maybe the server can send out a rpc event when it starts which is received by all other currently running server and all of them update their serverlists. The shell command seems fine for unix systems but I'm not sure if there's something equivalent on windows? Also, I don't know whether it's a good idea to run shell commands in the code directly.\n\nThe rpc communication method would also help with the remote stuff, to list current servers on the remote instance when `:connect` is called.",
